  <h2>The "Winter Shock": Night Rebate Suspension</h2>

  <p>
    In a significant deviation from the standard RST Order, TSERC approved an amendment to suspend the
    night-time ToD rebate for December 2025 through March 2026. The rationale:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Thermal Backing Down Costs:</strong> During winter nights, demand crashes. Discoms must
    back down thermal stations to technical minimums, incurring compensation costs while still paying
    for must-run renewables.</li>
    <li><strong>Revenue Gap:</strong> The rebate was causing a revenue leak during months when the system
    did not need load shifting (night demand is naturally low in winter).</li>
  </ul>

